<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARASSMENT AT NAVAL ACADEMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The command structure at Annapolis that countenanced the climate that led to 
the outrageous attack on Dreyer, then winked at the perpetrators, should be 
immediately reassigned. 
</P>
<P>
As for those "good-natured" midshipmen, participants and the gawkers who could 
have stopped the stupidity, let them see what it's like to be ordinary seamen 
for a year or two. Maybe by then they will have a better understanding of the 
damage they have done to Ms. Dreyer and be more worthy of becoming officers. 
</P>
<P>
FRED BENES 
</P>
<P>
Cambria 
</P>
