<P>
REPAVING TO CLOSE SIMI FREEWAY LANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two lanes of the westbound Simi Valley Freeway between Topanga Canyon Boulevard 
and Rocky Peak Road will be closed tonight and Saturday for paving, the 
California Department of Transportation reported. 
</P>
<P>
The lanes are scheduled to close at 8 p.m. tonight and reopen about 6 p.m. 
Saturday. The Topanga Canyon Boulevard on-ramp to the highway will be closed 
most of that time, Caltrans officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Caltrans advised motorists to use the De Soto Avenue on-ramp instead. 
</P>
