<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRST LADY'S SPEECH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have never actually had much interest in Barbara Bush but her refreshing 
speech at Wellesley College's commencement really impressed me (Part A, June 
2). 
</P>
<P>
As a university student, she reassures me that my values are set straight. She 
emphasizes her desire for women in the '90s to help create a better society. 
Also, she speaks of her passion for life (which shines through in this vital 
speech). But most of all, she urges the need for compassion for one another. I 
would be quite fortunate to follow in her footsteps. There is, after all, a 
heart in the White House. 
</P>
<P>
RANIA NAGULB 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 
</P>
