<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : OCEANSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oceanside man has been arrested on suspicion of murdering a Vista man who 
was shot to death May 31. Amos J. Johnson, 31, of the 200 block of Country Club 
Lane, was arrested at his home late Wednesday and is being held without bail at 
the County Jail in Vista. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies arrested Johnson in connection with the killing of Alexander 
Bazan, 25, of the 400 block of Sunrise Drive East. Bazan died of a single 
gunshot wound, Lt. John Tenwolde said. 
</P>
<P>
Tenwolde said Bazan was sitting in his car in a Vista restaurant parking lot at 
Sycamore Drive and California 78 when the shooting occurred shortly after 
midnight. Tenwolde said witnesses saw Johnson standing at Bazan's open car door 
on the driver's side. 
</P>
<P>
The two men were engaged in a struggle when Johnson pulled a handgun and shot 
Bazan in the chest, Tenwolde said. Bazan died at Palomar Medical Center about 
90 minutes after the shooting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
