NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mississippi State University officials say they will investigate allegations of 
on-campus betting and whether NCAA rules were violated, after a professor and a 
former student pleaded guilty to federal gambling charges. 
</P>
<P>
Court documents indicate three Mississippi State football players were used in 
the fall of 1987 to help collect gambling debts. The players were not named. 
</P>
