<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Superior Court judge in Paterson, N.J., Thursday cleared the way for a 
heavyweight title fight between champion Buster Douglas and Evander Holyfield 
by rejecting a request that would have prevented promoters from offering bids 
to stage the fight. 
</P>
<P>
Judge Amos C. Saunders' ruling caps a nearly three-month legal battle by 
Holyfield's attorney to prevent rival promoters from interfering with the bids 
for the championship fight. 
</P>
