<HEADLINE>
<P>
BETTING WITH BOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAN VS. MICROCHIP 
</P>
<P>
Perhaps, I should have gone to my brother for the money from the beginning 
rather than The Times. 
</P>
<P>
His mythical bills are obviously a little luckier. 
</P>
<P>
Indian Wind, the first bet I made Thursday, ran second, but was moved up to 
first on a controversial stewards' decision. On second thought, how could any 
decision that puts my horse on top be controversial? He paid $5.40, so my 
profit was $85. 
</P>
<P>
A race later, Vince's Dancer won clear at $6.20, so I collected another $155, 
meaning I'm $190 in the black after one day. You know, I'm beginning to like 
this job a lot better. 
</P>
<P>
Hoping to keep the streak going, I'll bet $40 to win on Rejim in the eighth. 
</P>
<P>
Bob's Beginning Bankroll $2,000 
</P>
<P>
Thursday's Profit $190 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $2,190 
</P>
<P>
As for my computer counterpart, its pick in the fifth, Reassured, won rather 
handily and paid $6.60, returning a profit of $57.50. In the seventh, it picked 
Dakotah Thunder, who ran fifth, reducing its profit to $32.50. 
</P>
<P>
The computer wants to bet $40 to win today on Por D.J. in the fifth. 
</P>
<P>
I wish the computer well, it'll need it. 
</P>
<P>
Computer's Beginning Bankroll $2,000 
</P>
<P>
Thursday's Profit $32.50 
</P>
<P>
Current Bankroll $2,032.50 
</P>
</TEXT>
