<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA; 
</P>
<P>
AZTEC PITCHERS PETERSEN, NIELSEN SIGN WITH ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego State pitchers Andy Petersen and Kevin Nielsen have signed contracts 
with St. Louis after the Cardinals picked them in the major league free agent 
draft this week. 
</P>
<P>
Petersen (10-2, 2.80 earned-run average in 1990) was a co-winner of SDSU's most 
valuable pitcher award. 
</P>
<P>
Nielsen was 4-4 with 4.81 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
Seven SDSU players have been drafted. Already signed are catcher Eric 
Christopherson (San Francisco), pitcher Kurt Archer (Milwaukee), outfielder 
Jeff Barry (Montreal), and pitcher Rusty Filter (Toronto). Pitcher Erik 
Plantenberg has reached a verbal agreement with Boston and is expected to sign 
on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego's Erik Judson, a senior shortstop who hit .300 and led the team in 
stolen bases this past season, was notified that he had been drafted by the 
Philadelphia Phillies, but he had not yet been contacted concerning a possible 
contract. 
</P>
<P>
GOLF 
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Phil Mickelson, a USDHS graduate from Arizona State, shot a 
four-under-par 68 to pull within four shots of the lead at the NCAA Division I 
men's championships at Innisbrook in Tarpon Springs, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
Mickelson is one of six players tied a one-under 143 after two rounds. 
Florida's Jeff Barlow remained the individual leader at 139 with a 71 Friday. 
</P>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOLS 
</P>
<P>
La Jolla Country Day named Daryl Ravani director of athletics and physical 
education, replacing Patrick Murphy, who will become vice principal at Santa 
Ana Mater Dei. Ravani, currently athletic director at Allendale-Columbia School 
in Rochester, N.Y., will take over July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
