<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
No Pipes of Peace for McCartney: Paul McCartney didn't let it be when he was 
called greedy by the manager of U2 just because he had a corporate sponsor -- 
Visa -- back his recent tour. McCartney responded with an eight-letter curse 
word. "My advice to Paul McGuinness is to grow up," McCartney said in Rolling 
Stone. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
