</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ann Curry Goes East: Ann Curry, who has been a reporter with KCBS-TV News since 
1984, has been hired as a correspondent for NBC News. Curry will initially be 
based in New York. She has won several awards, including an Emmy for live 
coverage of an unscheduled news event for the October, 1987, Whittier Narrows 
earthquake. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
