<TEXT>
<P>
Judge OKs Greyhound Expenses: A federal bankruptcy court judge authorized 
Greyhound Lines Inc. to pay salaries and operating expenses after union 
attorneys made sure the strike-bound bus company's executives would not receive 
"golden parachute" bonuses. At the hearing in Brownsville, Tex., U.S. 
Bankruptcy Court Judge Richard S. Schmidt ordered the U.S. Trustee's Office to 
start setting up a single committee of unsecured creditors. Greyhound filed 
Monday for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. 
</P>
