</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rockwell Reorganizes Unit: Rockwell International Corp. said it has reorganized 
its defense electronics operation again in a move aimed at further streamlining 
the business and boosting weapons sales in the U.S. and abroad. 
</P>
<P>
The move marks the third time since July that Rockwell has announced a 
reshuffling of its Anaheim-based Defense Electronics unit, which is headed by 
John A. McLuckey, group president. The changes will not result in any layoffs 
or relocations. The new organization allows the defense electronics group to 
more efficiently handle several major contract programs the company has won in 
the past several years. 
</P>
