<P>
EC Farm Ministers to Lift Beef Bans: European Community agriculture ministers 
reached agreement on tighter measures to curb "mad cow" disease and France, 
West Germany and Italy agreed to lift their bans on British beef imports. After 
an all-night emergency meeting, British minister John Gummer told reporters the 
bans, imposed because of concern that the cattle brain disease affects human 
health, would be lifted. Diplomats said the agreement, in classic Community 
style, would allow all sides to claim victory. 
