<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ORANGE; 
</P>
<P>
PUBLIC ASKED TO HELP FIND SLAYING SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police are asking for the public's help in finding a man suspected of stabbing 
to death an acquaintance in front of a restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
Arturo Rey Vega Rosas, 23, of Orange is wanted in the knifing of Pedro Rosas 
Hernandez, 24, also of Orange, said Sgt. Bob Gustafson. 
</P>
<P>
Police at first thought that Vega Rosas was headed toward Mexico after the May 
31 incident, but recently investigators received information that the suspect 
is still in Orange County, Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
Rosas Hernandez died in the parking lot of Claudia's restaurant on East Chapman 
Avenue after he apparently had an argument with Vega Rosas, Gustafson said. 
Vega Rosas allegedly pulled out a large knife and stabbed Hernandez several 
times, Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
Vega Rosas is described as 5 feet, 8 inches tall and weighing about 175 pounds. 
He has dark eyes, black shoulder-length hair and a light-colored mustache, 
Gustafson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Arturo Rey Vega Rosas 
</P>
