<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT / COMMERCIAL REAL ESTATE: FOCUS: BAYVIEW CORPORATE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has begun on a six-story office building that will complete the 
64-acre Bayview Corporate Center in Newport Beach. The complex already includes 
Downey Savings &amp; Loan's headquarters in an office building identical to the 
new one, a Marriott Suites hotel, restaurants, stores and two residential 
developments. 
</P>
<P>
The new building will have an exterior of imported granite and tinted glass. 
Inside, the lobby will feature a waterfall enclosed in a three-story atrium. A 
900-space, five-level parking structure will be built next to the office 
building. 
</P>
