<HEADLINE>
<P>
PPG IN JOINT VENTURE ON CONTACT LENSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PPG Industries said its Chemicals Group will form a joint venture with a French 
firm to manufacture and market special contact lenses, forming a new company 
that will be headquartered in St. Petersburg, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
PPG and Essilor International of France have reached an agreement in principle 
to make ophthalmic-quality lenses for consumer eye wear. 
</P>
<P>
PPG would hold 51% of the new company, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The deal is subject to approval by boards of directors of both companies. 
</P>
<P>
The new firm will make Transitions optical plastic photochromic lenses, which 
darken when exposed to sunlight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
