<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S MARATHON TEAM NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Budd Coates, Jerry Marsh and Mike Keohane have been named to the U.S. men's 
marathon team in this summer's Goodwill Games in Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
They were selected by The Athletics Congress based on performances between 
Sept. 30, 1989, and March 18, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Coates, 33, of Emmaus, Pa., won the California International Marathon in 
Sacramento with a time of 2 hours, 14 minutes, 7 seconds in December. 
</P>
<P>
Marsh, 26, of Santa Monica, was timed at 2:15:20 for third place at the same 
meet. Keohane, 25, Livingston, N.J., ran a 2:16.20 for fourth at the Columbus 
(Ohio) Marathon last November. 
</P>
<P>
In April, TAC announced the U.S. women's marathon team: Linda Somers, Rosa 
Gutierrez and Leslie Lewis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
