<P>
U.S. CUP SQUAD IS THE YOUNGEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROME 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States has the youngest squad of the 24 finalists in the World Cup, 
and Ireland has the oldest. 
</P>
<P>
The Americans, with midfielder Chris Henderson the tournament's youngest player 
and only teen-ager at 19, average 23.6 years of age. 
</P>
<P>
The nine players aged over 30 in Ireland's 22-strong squad raised their average 
to 28.9 years. Only two other teams in the tournament, the Soviet Union and 
England, have squads with an average age over 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
